  "texts": [
    "Although model size played a critical role in this development (Chowdhery et al. 2023), smaller, encoder-based PLMs have also been successfully applied in few-shot scenarios using promptbased fine-tuning in combination with a semi-supervised approach (Schick and Schütze 2021b; Wang et al. 2022).",
    "Especially, framing text classification tasks as cloze-style problems using pattern-exploiting training (PET) showed promising results for various classification tasks (Schick and Schütze 2022) (cf.",
    "Section 2).",
    "Domain adaptation through further-pretraining.",
    "Further-pretraining means training an already pretrained language model further on domain-specific texts using a language model objective."
  ],
